# include/

This directory contains the public header files for the project, organized by component. Each subfolder corresponds to a major component of the language and exposes its public API.

## Subfolders

### lexer/
Contains header files for the lexical analysis component.  
These headers define the API for tokenizing source code, handling character streams, and managing token types.

### parser/
Contains header files for the parsing component.  
These headers define the API for syntactic analysis, grammar rules, and building parse trees from token streams.

### ast/
Contains header files for the Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) component.  
These headers define the API for representing, traversing, and manipulating the AST, which is used for further analysis and code generation.
### types/
Contains the header files for type definitions and file system utilities.  
This includes code for file handling, path manipulation, and other type-related utilities used throughout the project.

